Introduction

Base URL: http://moboeats.test

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Authenticating requests

This API is not authenticated.

Authentication Management

User API resource

Login through email and password

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://moboeats.test/api/v1/login" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"email\": \"may38@example.com\",
    \"password\": \"xl`*m|=;5^|\\\"R.}w^\\/\",
    \"userType\": \"architecto\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://moboeats.test/api/v1/login"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "email": "may38@example.com",
    "password": "xl`*m|=;5^|\"R.}w^\/",
    "userType": "architecto"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Request      

POST api/v1/login

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

email   string   

The email of the user Example: may38@example.com

password   string   

The password of the user Example: xl*m|=;5^|"R.}w^/`

userType   string   

The type of user Example: architecto

Registration

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://moboeats.test/api/v1/register" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"name\": \"yakdjsenndcsnox\",
    \"email\": \"jamil69@example.net\",
    \"password\": \")rq78p{i10(C\",
    \"userType\": \"est\",
    \"phone\": \"molestiae\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://moboeats.test/api/v1/register"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "name": "yakdjsenndcsnox",
    "email": "jamil69@example.net",
    "password": ")rq78p{i10(C",
    "userType": "est",
    "phone": "molestiae"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Request      

POST api/v1/register

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

name   string   

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: yakdjsenndcsnox

email   string   

The email of the user Example: jamil69@example.net

password   string   

The password of the user Example: )rq78p{i10(C

userType   string   

The type of user Example: est

otp   string  optional  
image   string  optional  
phone   string   

The type of user Example: molestiae

Forgot Password

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://moboeats.test/api/v1/forgot-password" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"email\": \"dawson.haag@example.org\",
    \"phone_number\": \"minima\"
}"

    "http://moboeats.test/api/v1/forgot-password"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",

Reset password

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://moboeats.test/api/v1/reset-password" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"code\": \"aut\",
    \"password\": \"31+W[HC\'F\\\"<BkA\",
    \"password_confirmation\": \"vel\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://moboeats.test/api/v1/reset-password"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "code": "aut",
    "password": "31+W[HC'F\"<BkA",
    "password_confirmation": "vel"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Request      

POST api/v1/reset-password

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

code   The  optional  

Verification OTP code Example: aut

password   The  optional  

new password to be set Example: 31+W[HC'F"<BkA

password_confirmation   The  optional  

new password confirmation Example: vel

Verify OTP

curl --request POST \
    "http://moboeats.test/api/v2/login/otp/verify" \

    \"code\": \"pariatur\",

}"

Request      

POST api/v1/orderer/orders

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

cartId   integer  optional  

Example: 8

restaurantId   integer   

Example: 20

delivery   boolean   

Example: false

delivery_address   string  optional  

This field is required when delivery is true.

delivery_location_lat   string  optional  

This field is required when delivery is true.

delivery_location_lng   string  optional  

This field is required when delivery is true.

booking_time   string  optional  

This field is required when delivery is false. Must be a valid date in the format Y-m-d H:i. Must be a date after 2024-05-31 15:38:22. Example: 2076-07-05

Request      

POST api/v1/orderer/order/reviews/store

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

order_id   integer  optional  

The id of the order Example: 13

restaurant_rating   integer  optional  

The rating of the restaurant from 1 - 5 Example: 14

restaurant_review   string  optional  

A review of the restaurant Example: mollitia

rider_rating   integer  optional  

The rating of the rider from 1 - 5 Example: 17

rider_review   string  optional  

A review of the rider Example: est

Send a message

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://moboeats.test/api/v1/message/send" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"receiver_id\": 14,
    \"message\": \"eum\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://moboeats.test/api/v1/message/send"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "receiver_id": 14,
    "message": "eum"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (201):


{}
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

    "http://moboeats.test/api/v1/menu"
);

const params = {
    "categories": "expedita",
    "subCategories": "similique",
    "restaurant": "iure",
};
Object.keys(params)
    .forEach(key => url.searchParams.append(key, params[key]));

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

    "http://moboeats.test/api/v1/restaurant/menu"
);

    "categories": "et",
    "subCategories": "rem",

};

Create Rider Profile

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://moboeats.test/api/v1/rider/profile/create" \
    --header "Content-Type: multipart/form-data" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --form "vehicle_type=neque" \
    --form "vehicle_license_plate=doloremque" \
    --form "paypal_email=irma75@example.com" \
    --form "vehicle_licesne_plate=distinctio" \
    --form "city=quia" \
    --form "state=voluptatem" \
    --form "postal_code=impedit" \
    --form "profile_picture=@C:\Users\ideaPad S340\AppData\Local\Temp\php6F19.tmp" 
const url = new URL(
    "http://moboeats.test/api/v1/rider/profile/create"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "multipart/form-data",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

const body = new FormData();
body.append('vehicle_type', 'neque');
body.append('vehicle_license_plate', 'doloremque');
body.append('paypal_email', 'irma75@example.com');
body.append('vehicle_licesne_plate', 'distinctio');
body.append('city', 'quia');
body.append('state', 'voluptatem');
body.append('postal_code', 'impedit');
body.append('profile_picture', document.querySelector('input[name="profile_picture"]').files[0]);

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body,
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (200):


{}
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.
